title: -Elastic and Inelastic Scattering of Neutrons In The Energy Range 2 To 5 Mev By B-10 and B-11.-

x4codes.hlp: Atomic Weapons Establishment (AWE), Aldermaston, United Kingdom

x4freetext: PREPRINT TO NUCL.PHYS.
-ELASTIC AND INELASTIC SCATTERING OF NEUTRONS IN THE
ENERGY RANGE 2 TO 5 MEV BY B-10 AND B-11.-
AWRE 6 MV VAN DE GRAAFF ACCELERATOR.
UP TO 4.312 MEV, T(P,N) REACTION, TRITIUM
GAS TARGET AT 760 TORR PRESSURE WITH AN 0.0003 CM
THICK MO ENTRANCE FOIL,
FOR HIGHER ENERGY, D(D,N) REACTION WITH A
SIMILAR TARGET CELL.
BY THE SPECIAL CARE FOR RUNS USING D-D NEUTRON SOURCE
AND BY OPTIMIZING THE BEAM TRANSMISSION, SYNCHRONOUS
BACKGROUNDS OF NEUTRONS WERE KEPT TO  A MINIMUM, IE,
+- 2.5 PER CENT OF THE 0 DEG NEUTRON YIELD.
THE INCIDENT N-ENERGIES, 2.0, 2.5, 3.0, 3.5, 4.0 MEV
BY T(P,N) AND 4.5, 5.0 MEV BY D(D,N) ARE NOMINAL
VALUES AND THESE VALUES HAVE BEEN CORRECTED AFTER
COMPLETION OF THE MEASUREMENT.  THE ERROR LIMITS ON
THESE N-ENERGIES ARE A COMBINATION OF THE ENERGY LOSS
IN THE GAS CELL AND CALIBRATION UNCERTAINTIES.
.ISOTOPICALLY ENRICHED BORON POWDER IN
ANNULAR CYLINDRICAL ALUMINIUM CANS,
.THE WALL THICKNESS WAS 0.025 CM AND THE
INTERNAL DIMENSIONS WERE, HEIGHT = 5.05 +- 0.09 CM,
INNER DIAMETER = 2.498 +- 0.005 CM, OUTER DIAMETER =
.ISOTOPIC COMPOSITION,
FOR B-10, 92.29 PER CENT B-10 7.71 PER CENT B-11,
FOR B-11, 92.66 PER CENT B-11 7.34 PER CENT B-10.
.THE ESTIMATE OF THE AMOUNT OF HYDROGEN
CONTAMINATION IS (4.8 PER CENT H BY ATOM IN B-11 AND
1.8 PER CENT H BY ATOM IN B-10).
TIME OF FLIGHT, FLIGHT PATH = 1.747 M,
TIME RESOLUTION IN THE TOF SPECTRA WAS BROADENED BY
LARGE DIMENSIONS OF SCATTERING SAMPLES, BUT WAS
SUFFICIENT TO RESOLVE THE 1ST EXCITED STATE IN B-11
AT ALL ENERGIES USED.  IN B-10, NEUTRONS SCATTERED TO
THE 1ST EXCITED STATE WERE ONLY SATISFACTORILY
RESOLVED AT TWO LOWEST ENERGIES.
LIQUID SCINTILLATOR (NE213), SEE TOWLE AND
WALL,NUCL.PHYS.A118(1968)500.
.THE ELASTIC ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS WERE
COMPARED WITH A NON-LOCAL OPTICAL MODEL,
.THE DIFFERENTIAL AND INTEGRATED INELASTIC
CROSS SECTIONS WERE COMPARED WITH HAUSER-FESHBACH
THEORY WITH FLUCTUATIONS (HFW), USING OPTICAL
POTENTIAL FROM THE ELASTIC ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION-FIT
WITH ESTIMATES OF OPTICAL POTENTIALS FOR (N,P), (N,T)
AND (N,A).
HORSLEY, NUCL.DATA 2(1966)243,
AT EACH INCIDENT ENERGY, THE SCATTERING AT 45 DEG FROM
HYDROGEN IN POLYTHENE SAMPLES WAS MEASURED.
BY RIGHTS THE OPTICAL MODEL SHOULD NOT APPLY AT THESE
ENERGIES IN LIGHT NUCLEI. AND IT APPEARS THAT SIMPLE
OPTICAL MODEL AND COMPOUND NUCLEUS CALCULATIONS OF
ELASTIC AND INELASTIC SCATTERING IN B-10 AND B-11 AT
THESE LOW ENERGIES ARE NOT PARTICULARLY USEFUL.  THE
BEST   OPTICAL MODEL POTENTIALS FROM FITS TO THE
ELASTIC SCATTERING DATA DO NOT SHOW ANY SYSTEMATIC
ENERGY DEPENDENCE BUT FLUCTUATE RATHER WILDLY.
CALCULATED TOTAL NEUTRON ELASTIC SCATTERING
CROSS-SECTION.
.FROM TABLE 5 OF AWRE-O-45/70.
IN CALCULATING CROSS SECTIONS, CORRECTIONS WERE MADE
FOR FLUX ATTENUATION AND MULTIPLE SCATTERING USING
THE MONTE CARLO CODE PROGRAM   MAGGIE  .
.FOR ELASTIC PEAK ESTIMATES, (A) CONTAMINATION NEUTRONS
(B) ENERGY REDUCTION OF ELASTICALLY SCATTERED NEUTRON
BY LIGHT NUCLEI MULTIPLE COLLISION (SHIFT TO INELASTIC
REGION OF THE TIME SPECTRUM), (C) THE SCATTERED
NEUTRONS FROM THE COLLIMATOR-WALL, (D) RANDOM COUNTS
DUE TO ELECTRONIC NOISE AND BACKGROUND NEUTRONS AND
GAMMAS,
WERE CONSIDERED TO BE CORRECTED.
THE ERROR REPRESENTS ONE STANDARD DEVIATION, THEY ARE
A COMBINATION OF THE RELATIVE ERRORS (STATISTICS, N-
DETECTOR EFFICIENCY AND OTHER SOURCES) AND THE
ABSOLUTE ERROR FROM THE NORMALISATION TO THE HYDROGEN
AND UNCERTAINTIES FROM THE SAMPLE COMPOSITION AND
IMPURITIES PLUS THE EFFECT OF THE AL CAN SCREENING.

CROSS-SECTION.
.FROM TABLE 6 OF AWRE-O-45/70.
IN CALCULATING CROSS SECTIONS, CORRECTIONS WERE MADE
FOR FLUX ATTENUATION AND MULTIPLE SCATTERING USING
THE MONTE CARLO CODE PROGRAM   MAGGIE  .
.FOR ELASTIC PEAK ESTIMATES, (A) CONTAMINATION NEUTRONS
(B) ENERGY REDUCTION OF ELASTICALLY SCATTERED NEUTRON
BY LIGHT NUCLEI MULTIPLE COLLISION (SHIFT TO INELASTIC
REGION OF THE TIME SPECTRUM), (C) THE SCATTERED
NEUTRONS FROM THE COLLIMATOR-WALL, (D) RANDOM COUNTS
DUE TO ELECTRONIC NOISE AND BACKGROUND NEUTRONS AND
GAMMAS,

THE ERROR REPRESENTS ONE STANDARD DEVIATION, THEY ARE
A COMBINATION OF THE RELATIVE ERRORS (STATISTICS, N-
DETECTOR EFFICIENCY AND OTHER SOURCES) AND THE
ABSOLUTE ERROR FROM THE NORMALISATION TO THE HYDROGEN
AND UNCERTAINTIES FROM THE SAMPLE COMPOSITION AND
IMPURITIES PLUS THE EFFECT OF THE AL CAN SCREENING.
